# Guardian Academy Environment Configuration

## Firebase Setup (Optional)

For cloud persistence to Firestore, copy this to `.env.local` in `apps/web/`:

```bash
# Firebase Project Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://your-project.firebaseio.com

# Service Account for Backend (keep private!)
# Use only in server-side code or secure environments
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT={"type":"service_account","project_id":"your-project",...}
```

### Getting Firebase Credentials

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Create a project or select existing
3. Go to **Settings > Project Settings**
4. Copy `projectId` and `apiKey`
5. Go to **Settings > Service Accounts** to generate JSON key

---

## Local Development (Default)

If `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT` is not set:
- App uses **in-memory storage**
- Perfect for local development & testing
- Data resets on app restart
- No configuration needed ✅

---

## Mobile App Configuration

For `apps/mobile/.env`:

```bash
# Expo Configuration
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api
EXPO_PUBLIC_SCORING_ENGINE_URL=http://localhost:8081

# For production
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://guardian-academy.org/api
```

---

## Monorepo Scripts

All configured in root `package.json`:

```bash
npm run dev           # Web + Mobile
npm run dev:full      # Web + Mobile + Scoring + Audit + Standards watch
npm run dev:web       # Next.js only
npm run dev:mobile    # Expo only
npm run dev:scoring   # GI² engine compiler
npm run dev:audit     # Audit logger compiler
npm run build:all     # Build for production
npm run test:all      # Run all tests
npm run clean         # Clean & reinstall deps
npm run reset         # Full clean state
```

---

## TypeScript Paths

Configured in `tsconfig.json`:

```typescript
import { calculateGI2Score } from '@scoring/index';
import { logAuditEvent } from '@audit/index';
// Standards as data (future):
// import spec from '@standards/gi2-metrics.md';
```

---

## Development Tools

- **Web:** Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript 5
- **Mobile:** Expo 54, React Native 0.81, TypeScript 5
- **Scoring:** TypeScript 5, Node.js ≥18
- **Monorepo:** npm workspaces, concurrently

---

